Pat,

Delphi enhances the MS help model by allowing for searches and links across multiple help files.  It also has facilities for linking your own help files into the main Delphi help file through keywords.

The help files must be built the old fashioned way with a help development too and the MS help compiler.  Borland is offering as a special deal to developers the very excellent Forehelp tool for a very low price of $69 (I think).  

The online help for Delphi is excellent and very well structured.

